    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-12T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-12T12:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1293.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires at
                            London</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-12T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1913—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Aide mémoire presented today. I venture to say that the Foreign Office seems
                    entirely inclined to your views towards settling representation on the loan in
                    any of the ways suggested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
